":"1273","Colyton, Devon, England":"Colyton, Devon, England","Doddington Hall, Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Picot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Francois, Jacques, Jeanpaul, Luc, Pascal, Yves.  Spanish Esperanza, Aida, Alicia, Ana, Felipe, Luis.","French: from Old French <i>picot</i> ‘pointed object, pickaxe’, a nickname for someone who used such an implement. This surname is also found in Haiti.","Catalan: nickname from Valencian dialect <i>picot</i> ‘(sheep or goat) bell’."],"variants":[{"name":"Pickett","meanings":["English:","from the Middle English, Old French personal name <i>Picot</i>, <i>Pigot</i>, a pet form of <i>Pic</i> (see   Pike   6). In Middle English, the form <i>Piket</i> (Old French <i>Picquet</i>) was also common.","sometimes a late development of   Pickard   1 or 2."]},{"name":"Picotte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Honore, Andre, Jacques, Serge.","Altered form of French   Picot  , reflecting the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>."]}]},{"name":"Michael","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of a common biblical name (meaning ‘who is like God?’ in Hebrew) borne by one of the archangels, the protector of the ancient Hebrews, who is also regarded as a saint of the Catholic Church. In the Middle Ages, Michael was regarded as captain of the heavenly host (see Revelation 12:7–9), symbol of the Church Militant, and patron of soldiers. He was often depicted bearing a flaming sword. The name is also borne by a Persian prince and ally of Belshazzar mentioned in the Book of Daniel. Since the early 1900s it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names in the English-speaking world.  See also  Michal ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":17,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Michael Picot was born in 1242, in Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England, his father, Pouncey Picot, was 8 and his mother, daughter of Henry Dyve, was 5. He married Joan Wake about 1285. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died before 12 November 1278, in Colyton, Devon, England."},"et":{"1242–before 12 November 1278":"1242–enne 12. novembrit 1278","1242–1278":"1242–1278","1255–1300":"1255–1300","–Female":"Surnud","1273–Female":"1273–Surnud","1284–Male":"1284–Surnud","1286–Male":"1286–Surnud","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1237–Female":"1237–Surnud","1259":"1259","1237":"1237","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1242":"1242","before 12 November 1278":"enne 12. novembrit 1278","1286":"1286","Aft 1273":"pärast 1273","1284":"1284","1273":"1273","Colyton, Devon, England":"Colyton, Devon, England","Doddington Hall, Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"1242–before 12 November 1278":"1242–ennen vuotta 12. marraskuuta 1278","1242–1278":"1242–1278","1255–1300":"1255–1300","–Female":"Kuollut","1273–Female":"1273–Kuollut","1284–Male":"1284–Kuollut","1286–Male":"1286–Kuollut","1235–Male":"1235–Kuollut","1237–Female":"1237–Kuollut","1259":"1259","1237":"1237","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1242":"1242","before 12 November 1278":"ennen vuotta 12. marraskuuta 1278","1286":"1286","Aft 1273":"1273 jälkeen","1284":"1284","1273":"1273","Colyton, Devon, England":"Colyton, Devon, England","Do